data.title: It is what it is
data.text: It is almost an old school dinner the food is great and fulling. I can say if you want to be filled up make sure that you eat the MESS it is a great dish of hash browns onions peppers spices and all the breakfast meats... With eggs.... It looks like a mess but it is divine breakfast is the best.

data.title: Tommy's Cafe is not very good
data.text: We ate here after a friend recommended it. First appearance, the place if falling apart and needs to be modernized with seats and tables that aren't falling apart. Silverware was dirty, floating items in our water, coffee was weak. We wanted something on the menu that wasn't 2,000 calories, but couldn't find anything. So we made it up and ordered 1 simple chicken breast, homestyle potatoes and coffee. $12-$15 for this simple $6 meal. I inquired with the boss if this was a misprint on the receipt, she said the cost of chicken is through the roof and it might even go up. Sorry, an entire cooked chicken at Costco or Fred Meyer cost $6 and last I checked potatoes were $5 for 10 lbs. That said, the chicken was overcooked and the amount of spuds provided was very little. Coffee was watered down and condiments included salt, pepper which actually gave the chicken and spuds some flavor. I will never come back here, thank you Tommy's for helping me choose McDonald's over you.

data.title: Family friendly
data.text: Tommy's has been there it seems like for ever.  It is an old fashion good food place.  You see the same people there every time you go in for breakfast. Their salad bar is a little sparse, but that leaves room for the good main course.  I never leave with a dogie bag, the food is that good there is nothing to take home.

data.title: Awful food & Atmosphere
data.text:
Stopped to eat a late breakfast around 10 or so and, with a McDonald's across the street, i made the wrong choice! I ordered a pretty simple breakfast of 2 eggs, hash browns & bacon and knew the moment it was put down in front of me how badly i erred stopping here to eat.  Bacon was a dark, ugly brown color as if it had been sitting on a side section of the grill for a few hours and ultra fatty. I cut into the over-medium eggs and that clear, whitish egg liquid poured out all over the plate. One nibble on the bacon was enough to make me want to immediately spit it out....but i forced it down with a big gulp of the slightly warm coffee i was served. Only the hash browns looked palatable but i wouldn't touch once the egg whites soaked into them.....
I would fast for a month instead of giving this place another try!!!

I HIGHLY recommend avoiding this place & choose a bacon, egg & cheese bisquit at McDonald's instead!  Awful experience.....

data.title: We won't be back
data.text:
We have visited Tommy's twice since my February review.  Our second visit left us feeling somewhat less than pleased, but decided to give them another try this weekend.
First impression---someone needs to do some cleaning, especially the glass main entrance.  I ordered pancakes and couldn't understand how they could be so completely tasteless.  Can you make pancakes with water?  I certainly detected no buttermilk.  My husband asked for his eggs medium, but the white wasn't even set and his hashbrowns were burnt. The staff is friendly and the prices aren't bad, but we are done.  We won't be returning.

data.title: Great Place for a Cafe-Style Breakfast
data.text: Ingredients taste fresh and homemade. Service was a little slow, but still good. I would eat there again.

data.title: Tommy's has the best breakfast in the area
data.text: Tommy's can be loud and busy with long wait to get in but the food and service is the best.  There may not be a lot of servers working but the ones they have are on top of everything and very efficient.  I have never had a coffee cup go dry and the food is always very good.  Sunday breakfast is the busiest of times, especially once church is over.

data.title: Terrific old style breakfast
data.text: Be sure to get Lynn for your server.  She has been at Tommys for twenty three years and is great.  Good basic cafe food - served hot and fast.  Very popular place for locals.

data.title: Pleasant diner experience
data.text:
This place would be easily accessed from hwy 405 by driving north on Rainier Ave in Renton.
We have lived in the area for years but this was our first visit.  Breakfast with friends and we all left happily.  I was pleased with the menu since one offering was the Mini--my perfect size, 1 egg, hash browns and 2 strips of bacon, with toast. The hash browns were crisp on top, nicely cooked and not at all greasy. We will stop in again.

data.title: OK
data.text: Just another understaffed mom and pop diner.  One waitress to handle the entire place at lunch time.  food was very good but I did not think the club sandwich was worth 10.00

data.title: Stereotypical diner
data.text: Tommy's is an old-school diner - if you want solid, diner-style food and don't expect frills you won't be disappointed.  Breakfasts are very busy, especially on the weekends but worth the wait.

data.title: "regular sunday"
data.text:
i love Tommy's restaurant!  the service is top notch, and the food is great and reasonable.

It's not fancy in decor, but the ambiance is the best.   Try the mini breakfast, it's  just enough to fill you up, the pancakes are huge and the french toast savory.  We frequent quite often on Sundays for breakfast.

data.title: Very Friendly Home Town Cafe
data.text: The Breakfasts are very good.  Hash browns especially, as they are freshly made!  Yummy French Toast, and bacon, too.  I haven't eaten many other meals there, mostly breakfasts and they are great.  Coffee cups are always being filled, without asking.  Wonderful service!  No waiting, just walk in and find a table.  The servers will find you and get you what you want....fast!

data.title: Typical greasy spoon!
data.text: Place is stuck in the 80s, food was average. Service was good. Not much to choose from in Renton. Better than Denny's or IHOP, though!

data.title: Great place for a decent meal.
data.text: Tommy's is a throw back to how I imagine cafes being in the 60's. Really friendly staff with average food, but great atmosphere!

data.title: Great breakfast place
data.text: This type of community cafe is wonderful.  The customers who know their neighbors and the workers by name is fun to watch. The generations of families that come to eat together is true small town America. Grandparents with grandchildren who climb up and down and up and down are welcome, as well as the single older persons and any size family.  The food is great breakfast, and the service comes with a smile and humor if you want to engage with it. Pancakes were wonderful!

data.title: Typical Diner-esque Food and Decor
data.text: But plenty of food. Great for breakfast and lunch. Very friendly service. Delicious omelets and coffee.

data.title: Fantastic friendly service
data.text: A great stop for a hearty breakfast.. Very friendly and attentive wait staff. I always had a refill of coffee without asking.  All of our breakfasts were tasty and very well done.

data.title: Good food...Great prices
data.text: A throw back to the old café diners. My wife and I visit Tommy's a few times each year. She likes the breakfasts (served anytime). I always go for the Salmon dinner ($12.99 at this writing). It comes with baked potato (choice of several trimmings), vegetable, and salad bar. The salmon is always generous and perfectly cooked. They seem to have lots of regulars. It's not a fancy restaurant, but it is always clean, and the service is always friendly.

data.title: Good family restaurant.
data.text: Regular customer. You can order anything all day. We enjoy the family atmosphere and the typical American menu. Their teriyaki steak is quite good. We often order vegetable fettuccine which is not on the menu any longer. Being seniors, we nearly always split a meal. The building is old,but so are we.
